ol.li:
Costs that should be excluded from the cost of inventories and expensed in the period incurred include: (IPSAS 12.25)
Abnormal amounts of wasted materials, labour, or other production costs;
Storage costs, unless those costs are necessary in the production process before a further production stage;
Administrative overheads that that do not contribute to bringing inventories to their present location and condition;
Selling costs.
